---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Matterport Pro 3 vs Pro 2: Complete 2025 Comparison"
  description="Detailed comparison of Matterport Pro 3 and Pro 2 scanners. Pro 3 is 2.75x more accurate (±20mm vs ±55mm), 2x faster, with 10x more points. See which is right for your project."
  keywords="matterport pro 3 vs pro 2, matterport pro 2, matterport comparison, matterport pro 3"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen">
    <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-900 to-blue-700 text-white py-20">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">Matterport Pro 3 vs Pro 2: Complete Comparison</h1>
        <p class="text-xl max-w-3xl">Updated for 2025 - See why we upgraded to Pro 3</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-5xl">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12 text-center text-gray-900">Quick Comparison</h2>
        
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full bg-white border border-gray-200">
            <thead class="bg-gray-50">
              <tr>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-center font-bold bg-blue-50">Pro 3 (Latest)</th>
                <th class="px-6 py-4 text-center font-bold">Pro 2</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="divide-y">
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Accuracy</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>±20mm @ 10m</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">±55mm @ 10m</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Accuracy Improvement</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>2.75x MORE ACCURATE</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">-</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Points per Scan</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>10x more</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">Standard</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Scan Speed</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>2x faster</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">Slower</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Battery Life</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>2.5 hours</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">1.5 hours</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Connectivity</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>Wi-Fi 6, BT 5.0</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">Wi-Fi 5, BT 4.2</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Processing</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>AI-powered (faster)</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">Standard cloud</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold">Best For</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center bg-green-50"><strong>BIM, Architecture, Professional</strong></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-center">Basic virtual tours</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">Key Differences Explained</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-blue-600 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3">1. Accuracy: ±20mm vs ±55mm (2.75x Better)</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">
              <strong>This is the most important difference.</strong> Pro 3's ±20mm accuracy vs Pro 2's ±55mm makes it suitable for professional scan-to-BIM and architectural applications where precision matters.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
              <strong>Why it matters:</strong> For BIM modeling and renovation projects, the improved accuracy means fewer measurement errors and better Revit model quality.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-gray-300 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3">2. Point Density: 10x More Points</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">Pro 3 captures 10x more points per scan than Pro 2, resulting in higher-detail 3D models.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm"><strong>Result:</strong> Smoother surfaces, better detail capture, more professional-looking tours.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-gray-300 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3">3. Speed: 2x Faster Scanning</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">Pro 3 completes scans in half the time of Pro 2.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm"><strong>Result:</strong> Less time on-site, faster project completion, lower costs.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white border-l-4 border-gray-300 p-6">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3">4. Battery: 2.5 hours vs 1.5 hours</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-2">67% longer battery life enables all-day scanning sessions.</p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm"><strong>Result:</strong> Can complete larger properties in single visit.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">Why We Use Matterport Pro 3</h2>
        
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-600 rounded-lg p-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 mb-4">
            <strong>We upgraded our entire fleet to Matterport Pro 3 because accuracy is critical for our clients.</strong>
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mr-2 text-xl">•</span>
              <span><strong>2.75x more accurate measurements</strong> = Better for BIM and architectural projects</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mr-2 text-xl">•</span>
              <span><strong>10x more point density</strong> = Higher quality virtual tours</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mr-2 text-xl">•</span>
              <span><strong>Faster projects</strong> = Lower costs passed to clients</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-blue-600 mr-2 text-xl">•</span>
              <span><strong>Latest features</strong> = Future-proof deliverables</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4 italic">
            "We don't use outdated equipment. All our virtual tours are captured with Matterport Pro 3 for the best possible results."
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16 bg-gray-50">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8 text-gray-900">When Pro 2 Might Be Sufficient</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          While we exclusively use Pro 3, some providers still offer Pro 2. It may be adequate for:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
          <li>• Very small properties (<1,000 sq ft)</li>
          <li>• Basic marketing virtual tours (not for BIM)</li>
          <li>• Budget-conscious projects</li>
          <li>• Quick residential listings</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-6">
          <strong>However:</strong> For professional applications, scan-to-BIM, architectural documentation, or projects requiring precision, Pro 3 is worth the investment.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-16">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-4 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4 text-gray-900">Experience the Matterport Pro 3 Difference</h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">All our virtual tours use the latest Pro 3 for superior accuracy and quality</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white px-8 py-4 rounded-lg font-bold text-lg">
          Get Your Virtual Tour
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

